gomodel:SYNGO_5030  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2, 3: Overexpression of VLDLR significantly increases, while knockdown of VLDLR decreases, dendritic spine number in primary hippocampal cultures.\n\nFigure 4, 5: Knockdown of VLDLR decreases GluN1 levels, cell surface GluA1 levels.\n\nFigure 6: VLDLR requires RasGRF1 to mediate dendritic spine density.\n\nFigure 7: VLDLR interacts with CaMKIIα and requires both CaMKIIα and CaMKIIβ to alter dendritic spine formation.. Experimental description: M&M: \"VLDLR knockout mice were raised from stocks originally created through targeted gene deletion [13]. All experiments used wild-type littermates as controls.\"\n\n\"The VLDLR shRNA constructs were a gift from Dr. Tracy Young-Pearse. The following was the target sequence for VLDLR shRNA #1: 5' -CCGGCCAGCAATGAACCTTGTGCTACTCGAGTAGCACAAGGTTCATTGCTGGTTTTTG-3', for VLDLR #3: 5'-CGGGCCGAGTCTGATCTTCACTAACTCGAGTTAGTGAAGATCAGACTCGGCTTTTTG-3' and the shRNAs were expressed in a pLKO.1 plasmid vector. The CaMKIIα and β RNAi constructs were gifts from Dr. Dan Pak at Georgetown University.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-18" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5030" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

